<poml>
  <meta>
    <id>poml.horse.seed.prompt</id>
    <version>0.1.0</version>
    <owner>atl</owner>
  </meta>

  <role>
    Kickstart automation for poml-horse: build a POML-first diagram pipeline, modular Go adapter, and deck.gl/luma.gl isometric MVP.
  </role>

  <task caption="Brief for OpenAI/Codex"><![CDATA[
  - Read `seed.poml` for schema/architecture/work plan and sample diagram.
  - Extend poml-go-sdk with diagram structs + validation and scene JSON exporter (nodes/edges/style/camera/layers).
  - Implement deck.gl/luma.gl viewer consuming scene JSON with isometric camera; export SVG/PNG.
  - Optional: Graphviz exporter; prepare hooks for Three.js/glTF.
  - Target: reach ~50% of MVP (parse POML diagram, emit scene JSON, render a basic isometric graph with good aesthetics).
  ]]></task>

  <task caption="Overall lead">
    Commandant – ultimate owner for delivery across all squads; resolves conflicts, sets priorities, accepts milestones.
  </task>

  <task caption="Stable personas (pommel theme, team effort)">
    Stablemaster (director) – keeps phases aligned and unblocks work across SDK/renderers/converters.
    Vault Captain (pipeline/CI) – enforces tests/fixtures, keeps scene export contracts green.
    Saddlewright (SDK core) – builds diagram AST, validation, scene exporter; guards unknown-tag tolerance.
    Ring Cartographer (renderers) – owns deck.gl/luma.gl view and Graphviz fallback; defines style contracts.
    Farrier (converters) – forges markdown/org ↔ POML converters; ensures minimal CDATA and clean round-trips.
    Groom (fixtures) – tends sample diagrams/goldens; adds variants (chain/star/grid) for coverage.
    Trail Scout (research) – monitors external references (e.g., microsoft/poml docs) for alignment and gaps.
    Trick Rider (experiments) – explores optional routes (Three.js, glTF) without blocking the core.
    Arena Judges (QA) – distrustful bug-hunters; design adversarial tests, fuzz inputs, and challenge architecture choices to expose fragility early.
  </task>

  <task caption="Team rosters (horse/cavalry theme)">
    QA – The Inspecting Cavalry:
      Cavalry Marshal (QA Lead)
      Arena Adjutant (Test Architect)
      Shock Trooper (Adversarial Tester)
      Horsebreaker (Fuzzing Specialist)
      Drill Sergeant (Automation Engineer)
      Dragoon (Performance Tester)
      Mountie (Security QA)
      Quartermaster (Data/Fixtures)
      Standard Bearer (Reporting/Quality Gate)
    SWENG – The Engineering Regiment:
      Captain of the Lines (Tech Lead)
      Lancer (Backend)
      Farrier (SDK/Parsing)
      Outrider (Frontend/Viewer)
      Scribe Cavalier (Converters/Docs)
      Bridgemaster (Integrations)
      Saddlewright (Tooling/CI Scripts)
      Proving Ground Officer (Testing-in-dev)
      Signal Corps (Code Health/Lint)
    INFRA – The Remount Corps:
      Stablemaster (Infra Lead)
      Vault Captain (CI/CD)
      Beacon Rider (Observability)
      Mountie (Security/Secrets)
      Courier (Networking)
      Packhorse Steward (Storage/Artifacts)
      Wrangler (Cloud/K8s)
      Farrier Sergeant (Reliability)
      Track Judge (Cost/Performance)
  </task>

  <input name="schema_ref" required="true">
    docs/refs/poml-horse/seed.poml
  </input>

  <input name="adapter_goal" required="true">
    POML → Go scene exporter (renderer-agnostic) with plug-in interface for deck.gl/luma.gl, Graphviz, Three.js, Mermaid, glTF.
  </input>

  <input name="mvp_goal" required="true">
    Render an isometric graph from POML via deck.gl/luma.gl, export SVG/PNG; keep style variables in scene JSON.
  </input>

  <notes><![CDATA[
Private seed (do not publish). Use poml-go-sdk capabilities (unknown-tag preservation, XML/CDATA safety) as foundation; add diagram types incrementally. Theme suggestion: a whimsical gymnastics stable—keep it fun, crisp, and modular.
  ]]></notes>

  <style>
    <output format="markdown">
      <![CDATA[
      ## Prompt Summary
      - Tasks
      - Inputs
      - MVP target
      ]]>
    </output>
  </style>
</poml>
